The '''Elmer Smith Power Plant''' is a [[coal-fired power plant]] owned and operated by the city of [[Owensboro, Kentucky]]. It opened in 1964.
==History== It was announced in June 2018 that Elmer Smith will close by June 2020. This is due to Owensboro Municipal Utility Commission approving a contract with Big Rivers Electric to supply electricity for Owensboro.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://wfpl.org/market-forces-drive-another-kentucky-coal-power-plant-to-retire/|title=Market Forces Drive Another Kentucky Coal Power Plant To Retire|last=Velzer|first=Ryan Van|publisher=WFPL|date=June 26, 2018|accessdate=October 18, 2018}}</ref>
