'''Forbes Marshall''' is an Indian engineering and [[energy conservation]] solutions provider, especially for the process industry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/forbes-marshall-plans-to-step-up-export-business/article6558007.ece |title=Forbes Marshall plans to step up export business |publisher=Business Line |accessdate=14 November 2014}}</ref> Forbes Marshall makes steam engineering and control instrumentation products and solutions.<ref>{{cite web|title=HBR Case Study Alliance Management at Forbes Marshall|url=https://hbr.org/product/alliance-management-at-forbes-marshall/an/W11618-PDF-ENG}}</ref> Its origins trace to a venture by [[J. N. Marshall]] and [[Darius Forbes]] in [[Pune]] in the 1940s, with a factory established at Kasarwadi, Pune in 1958.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://parsikhabar.net/individuals/darius-forbes-and-forbes-marshall-building-up-industry/3648/|title=Darius Forbes and Forbes Marshall: Building Up Industry|publisher=Business World|accessdate=14 November 2014}}</ref> It is based in [[Pune]].

In 2013, Forbes Marshall was voted one of India's top ten best companies to work for.<ref>{{cite news|title=Forbes Marshall - India's top 10 best companies to work for - The Economic Times|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/slideshows/work-career/indias-top-10-best-companies-to-work-for/forbes-marshall/slideshow/20739907.cms|accessdate=19 January 2017|agency=The Economic Times|publisher=ET Bureau|date=24 June 2013}}</ref>

Forbes Marshall has four manufacturing units in India which are located at Kasarwadi, [[Pimpri]], [[Hyderabad]] and Chakan near Pune.<ref>{{cite news|title=Forbes Marshall-Vyncke JV sets up facility at Chakan|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/forbes-marshall-vyncke-jv-sets-up-facility-at-chakan-113121201068_1.html|accessdate=19 January 2017|work=Business Standard India|publisher=BS Reporter|date=12 December 2013}}</ref>

