'''Wind power in the Philippines''' makes up a small percentage of the total energy output of the [[Philippines]]. The country wind energy sector has significant potential and could provide up to 76GW of power. Some of the most recent developments are the [[Bangui Wind Farm]], [[Burgos Wind Farm]], and [[Caparispisan Wind Farm]] in [[Ilocos Norte]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.businessgreen.com/bg/news/1928862/philippines-sparks-wind-energy-gold-rush |title=Philippines sparks wind energy gold rush |publisher=businessGreen |date=30 November 2010 |author=Young, Tom |accessdate=30 June 2012}}</ref>, the [[Wind Energy Power System (Philippines Wind Farm)|Wind Energy Power System]] (WEPS) in Puerto Galera, Mindoro Oriental<ref>{{cite web|last=Evora|first=Robert|title=Mindoro Wind Farm Rising|url=http://www.phesi.net/Wpress/?p=473|publisher=Manila Standard Today}}</ref> and [[Pililla Wind Farm]] [[Pililla]], [[Rizal]].

